---
title: Buttered Rosemary Strip Steak with a Wedge Salad and Thyme-Roasted Potatoes
description: A steakhouse-worthy meal is totally do-able at home when you’ve got some top-notch ingredients. Which is why we’ve put a beautiful strip steak at the center of this meal, then surrounded it with classy accompaniments like herbed potatoes and a wedge salad with creamy dressing. It’s the sort of thing that feels like it was put together by a master grill chef, except this time, that chef is you.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/buttered-rosemary-strip-steak-5c1fd4b4.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/buttered-rosemary-strip-steak-59fb7d02d56afa406f3ba622-18dfeacb.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/buttered-rosemary-strip-steak-59fb7d02d56afa406f3ba622
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
cuisine: North America
time required: 40 minutes
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 780 kcal
  fat: 52 g
  saturated fat: 23 g
  carbohydrates: 46 g
  sugar: 9 g
  protein: 40 g
  fiber: 12 g
  sodium: 170 mg
---

Wash and dry all produce. Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Take out 2 TBSP @butter{2%tablespoon} and let sit at room temperature. Halve and peel @shallot{1}. Finely mince one half; thinly slice other. Halve @heirloom grape tomatoes{4%ounce}. Halve @lemon{1} and squeeze 1 TBSP juice into a #small bowl{}. Strip 2 tsp @thyme{¼%ounce} leaves from stems. Halve @fingerling potatoes{12%ounce} lengthwise.

Toss potatoes with a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{4%teaspoon}, stripped thyme, @salt{}, and @pepper{} on a #baking sheet{}. Roast in oven until tender and lightly browned, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Pick and finely chop enough @rosemary{¼%ounce} leaves from stems to give you ½ tsp. Using a #spoon{}, mix butter and 2 tsp minced shallot in another small bowl. Stir in chopped rosemary. Season with salt and pepper. Place bowl in refrigerator and let chill until ready to serve.

> If butter is not soft, microwave on high for 10 seconds.

Heat a large drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Pat @New York strip steak{12%ounce} dry with a #paper towel{}, then season generously all over with salt and pepper. Add to pan and cook to desired doneness, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Remove from pan and set aside to rest.

Stir @sour cream{4%tablespoon} and 1 tsp water into lemon juice in bowl. Season with salt and pepper. Place tomatoes and sliced shallot (to taste) in a #medium bowl{}. Season with salt and pepper, then toss to combine. Halve @romaine lettuce{1} lengthwise, then cut into thick wedges.

Divide romaine between plates, then scatter tomato and shallot mixture on top. Drizzle with sour cream mixture. Slice steak against the grain, then add to plates, along with potatoes. Dollop steak with herb butter and serve.